OL,6,FEarlier, Dryden's advocate Lili Prais
OL,7,FKC told the court he accepts "full
OL,8,Fresponsibility for the monstrous
OL,9,Fcrime", and is "deeply remorseful".
OL,11,FShe read out a written statement from
OL,12,FDryden in which he said: "No sentence
OL,13,FI get will justify or bring closure to
OL,14,Fher family.
OL,16,F"The despicable, monstrous crime I
OL,17,Fhave committed, I have turned
OL,18,Feveryone's life upside down.
OL,26,@oD@^OUqD@FO]qD@POUqD@bO]tD@ZOUxD@AOU
